[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/jacoby_2nt"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST should not be tempted to use Jacoby 2NT with this hand. There are only 12 points, and 
the Limit Raise is a perfect way to show a 12 point support hand.

EAST has more than enough strength to bid game after WEST's limit raise. If WEST had 
mistakenly used a Jacoby 2NT response, EAST would probably have tried to reach slam, 
and perhaps gotten too high.}

